âœª NoSQL databases
1ï¸âƒ£  Optimal workloads: Designed for various data access patterns, including low-latency applications and analytics over semi-structured data.ğŸš€
2ï¸âƒ£  Data model: Provides a variety of models like key-value, document, graph, and column optimized for performance and scale.ğŸ”‘
3ï¸âƒ£  ACID properties: Offers trade-offs by relaxing some ACID properties for more flexible data models.ğŸ”„
4ï¸âƒ£  Performance: Dependent on hardware cluster size, network latency, and calling application.ğŸš„
5ï¸âƒ£  Scale: Typically partitionable, enabling consistent performance at near-boundless scale.ğŸŒ
6ï¸âƒ£  APIs: Uses object-based APIs for storing and retrieving data structures.ğŸ”„
